	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002076_0001"/><!--pb/@n='9r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"> 30 Sept<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> 1864 
<lb/><!-- headed notepaper --></p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>You remember 
<lb/><persName>Captain Henry Need</persName>
<lb/>who lent us his 
<lb/>portfolio of drawings 
<lb/>made on the <placeName>West 
<lb/>Coast</placeName> &amp; whom 
<lb/>you pronounced 
<lb/>to have a real 
<lb/>artistic eye. Well 
<lb/>he is near to this 
<lb/>and very infirm 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002076_0002"/><!--pb/@n='9v'-->
<lb/>nothing would delight 
<lb/>him more than 
<lb/>doing any drawing 
<lb/>we need - that indeed 
<lb/>is the only thing 
<lb/>he can do now. So 
<lb/>when you have 
<lb/>decided on what 
<lb/>you like please 
<lb/>send them down 
<lb/>and he will make 
<lb/>any combination 
<lb/>of them you may 
<lb/>suggest. <choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002076_0003"/><!--pb/@n='10r'-->
<lb/>lip ring ladies who 
<lb/>were mentioned 
<lb/>by my brother might 
<lb/>be done by him if 
<lb/>you think it 
<lb/>advisable<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p><persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">rs</hi></hi> Webb</persName> &amp; her husband 
<lb/>would have been 
<lb/>better pleased if 
<lb/>I had reported 
<lb/>that you were 
<lb/>coming here soon. </p>
<lb/><p>I write this 
<lb/>morning to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Conyingham</persName> of the 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002076_0004"/><!--pb/@n='10v'-->
<lb/>Foreign Office for 
<lb/>the blue books in 
<lb/>which my despatches 
<lb/>are - if he complies 
<lb/>&amp; sends them to you 
<lb/>please do send them 
<lb/>by Rail down to 
<lb/><placeName>Newstead</placeName> which is 
<lb/>a private station 
<lb/>and oblige yours &amp;c. </p>
<lb/><p><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
